node.text: Hello. Today, Sunday had some sunshine but mostly rain....and I chose to stay right out there in our garden and keep tidying. But really these wee squares are about His creativity. A portion of a tree trunk (swipe to see) from our lovely neighbours is where it all began back in April. He stood and gazed at it for more than a few moments and then the magic began. Every morning He disappeared down the garden and ‘chipped away’. Over the days,the weeks this beautiful stool emerged. It needs only a little more and then it is ready to move on to its forever home....it needs to be forever as it’s bl***y heavy for mature folk to haul about! It kept Him sane during lockdown and thus kept me sane too. A win win thing! #wood #trees #woodworking #creativity #lockdown #sanity #beingoutdoors #project #evolving #organicshapes

node.text:
Ieri, #22Agosto, è stato l’#OvershootDay. 

Da ieri, dunque, abbiamo #consumato #tutte le #risorse che il Pianeta produce dall’inizio dell’anno. 

Da oggi siamo in #debito con la #Terra! 

L’anno scorso tale data è caduta il #29Luglio. 

Siamo stati #bravi? #No, in quanto ciò è stato possibile a causa del #lockdown che ha rallentato le attività produttive umane.

Serve un grande impegno da parte di tutti noi e dei governi nazionali, in modo da cambiare il paradigma, dato che ad oggi consumiamo come se avessimo a disposizione 1,7 pianeti. 

Ricordiamoci che la #Terra è #una sola!

node.text:
- PUERTO ESCONDIDO OAXACA, MEXICO,... NATURALMENTE.

The rider Jose Ramirez @joseramirezrito along with Photographer Omar Diaz @aguapesadaphotos whom I met in 1997 after moving to Puerto to start a new chapter in my life at 45 years old.

Jose was the best body boarder in town and Omar was one of the top young surfers of that Era.

It's all so amazing the guidence that mysteriously plays into our lives. Quite literally we are met with thousands of possibilities, chance encounters, recommendations, factoring into thousands more directional promptings.

I got a shot of Jose dropping in on a large Puerto barrel which I turned into a poster back in 2005. Omar had a Two Page Spread in Surfer Magazine @surfer_magazine in 1998 or so.

During the years living in Puerto I sold many hundreds of my surf photos as framed prints and rolled posters out of @bazarpuerto a surf, art and culture boutique owned by Jose and his amazing wife Roxel @roxel.perez.

I got a call from Omar one day at the family home in #California back in 1999. He asked if he could have a job with me,... after paddling across the border and into shore at #ImperialBeach. A routine which all the young Puerto surf crew did back then to get work and make connections in the USA during the off season at #mexpipe.

Those were the times when you could move back and forth with relative ease. My God I'm shaking my head over this current #lockdown and the sad loss of #HumanFreedom and #Travel that has occurred.

Omar spent a year or so helping me out mounting the photo film, building poster displays and inventory for the emerging poster business. In his off time he asked if he could look through my many volumes of slides, pouring through them for hours upon hours. When I see his photos today I can clearly see I have made a contribution to his life.

There are so many others to mention, all unique encounters that began when a 21 year old kid from Corona del Mar California decided that he must capture the surf and this miraculous Creation we share nearly 50 years ago.

More #PuertoEscondido history posts coming. Hit the Follow Tab and urge those who love #Surf, Puerto, #NaturalBeauty, #Freedom and #TRUTH to join us.

node.text:
📺 No one asked... but here are some of my favourite #lockdown streaming binges of the year. (Scroll down) Any recommendations for me? X
.
.

1: #Flowers- By #WillSharpe (#Netflix) Just wow. How have I only just found out about this show? Apparently it’s been floating about since 2016 but it’s two seasons of pure magic. I’d so love to speak with the mind that created this. Dark, witty, beautiful, otherworldly. But oh so real. (Realer than most, in fact.)
.

2: #Ozark (Netflix) This last season though! And the last episode? If you know, you know. (And apologies to anyone triggered by the picture. Me too.) Best season yet! Breaking Bad levels.

.
3: #Fleabag - by Phoebe Waller Bridge (#amazonprime ) Yes I watched it again. Because Phoebe. And because hot priest. And you know what? It bears repeating. (Killing Eve on Hulu, also by Phoebe, was brilliant too! Yes to more ladies in action thrillers!)
.

4: #LoveOnTheSpectrum (Netflix) Please watch this if you haven’t. An Aussie show documenting first dates of some brilliant young people on the autism spectrum. The dads talking about their kids got me every time. It ended too soon.
.

5. #RuPaulsDragRace Season 12 (Amazon Prime). A strong year indeed! 

.
6: #13th (Netflix) Not an easy watch. But a very necessary one. An education. 

.
7: #Parasite (Netflix) - finally got around to watching this Oscar winner. And I get totally why it won. It’ll creep up on you repeatedly long after you’ve watched it.

.
8: #TheGreat - (#hulu ) 
I literally joined Hulu to watch this on recommendation from @gabrielbenjamin9 (🙏🏻 you know me!) ... and it was worth every penny. And allll the ads. A part history lesson on Alexandra the Great, part Monty Python -totally making it all up-swearing farce... I loved it with my whole heart. Brilliant. These 2 kids were made for these characters so whether or not you have liked them in anything before, give this a go. Huzzah! 
.

9. #Unorthodox - (Netflix) A stunning piece of work. I was knocked out by Shira Haas’ performance. Based on a true story. Stick around for the ‘making of’.

.
10: #90DayFiance - (#hulu ) A guilty pleasure. I can’t stop watching it. Spend most of my time screaming at the 📺

Shobharam, a resident of Bayadipura in Manawar tehsil of Dhar district, was spotted by people at Dhar district headquarters on Tuesday morning when he reached the examination centre-- Bhoj Girls Higher Secondary School-- pedalling the bicycle with his son, a class 10 student, sitting on the frame of the cycle.

Shobharam said, “After the lockdown restrictions buses came to a halt. The buses are not operating even now. There was no one to help me at the village, hence I decided to come here on my bicycle. I left from Dhar on Sunday night itself and stayed overnight at Manawar town. I reached Mandu at 4 am on Tuesday and the exam centre at Dhar just 15 minutes before the examination was to begin.”

He said he will stay in Dhar till August 24 when his son’s examinations will get over. He has brought food grains and other essential items to cook meals stuffed in a gunny bag which he carried on the bicycle.

It took more than 8hours of cycling to get there.

👑
Furloughed from my job as a dental nurse and with year 2 of university completed, the Coronovirus stopped me in my tracks as it did for millions the world over. I suddenly had time to be bored, an experience that as a mother of 2 with a day job and a full time degree on the go I hadn’t experienced in a long time. They say boredom breeds creativity and this ongoing series is the result of just that. What started with this self portrait mixing my love of fashion and portraiture, evolved into ‘Quarantine Queens’ - a way to capture and celebrate women in these interesting and unsettling times

- PUERTO ESCONDIDO OAXACA, MEXICO,... NATURALMENTE.

The rider Jose Ramirez @joseramirezrito along with Photographer Omar Diaz @aguapesadaphotos whom I met in 1997 after moving to Puerto to start a new chapter in my life at 45 years old.

Jose was the best body boarder in town and Omar was one of the top young surfers of that Era.

It's all so amazing the guidence that mysteriously plays into our lives. Quite literally we are met with thousands of possibilities, chance encounters, recommendations, factoring into thousands more directional promptings.

I got a shot of Jose dropping in on a large Puerto barrel which I turned into a poster back in 2005. Omar had a Two Page Spread in Surfer Magazine @surfer_magazine in 1998 or so.

During the years living in Puerto I sold many hundreds of my surf photos as framed prints and rolled posters out of @bazarpuerto a surf, art and culture boutique owned by Jose and his amazing wife Roxel @roxel.perez.

I got a call from Omar one day at the family home in #California back in 1999. He asked if he could have a job with me,... after paddling across the border and into shore at #ImperialBeach. A routine which all the young Puerto surf crew did back then to get work and make connections in the USA during the off season at #mexpipe.

Those were the times when you could move back and forth with relative ease. My God I'm shaking my head over this current #lockdown and the sad loss of #HumanFreedom and #Travel that has occurred.

Omar spent a year or so helping me out mounting the photo film, building poster displays and inventory for the emerging poster business. In his off time he asked if he could look through my many volumes of slides, pouring through them for hours upon hours. When I see his photos today I can clearly see I have made a contribution to his life.

There are so many others to mention, all unique encounters that began when a 21 year old kid from Corona del Mar California decided that he must capture the surf and this miraculous Creation we share nearly 50 years ago.

More #PuertoEscondido history posts coming. Hit the Follow Tab and urge those who love #Surf, Puerto, #NaturalBeauty, #Freedom and #TRUTH to join us.

node.text:
I’m not one to share or upload quotes at all, because let’s be honest... they’re annoying as hell to scroll through 😅 but this may actually be helpful to anyone who suffers with Health Anxiety like I do...

This really did hit the nail on the head for me & just explains what I couldn’t explain myself, to anybody. The world has become such a SHOCKING place (it may have been like this for awhile, but I was able to hide away from it) but now it’s all being shoved in our faces day in, day out... it’s kinda hard to ignore it & to just be happy with the world.

It’s so easy to lose our way & go into panic mode with this place (especially people with anxiety)... but we all need to breathe, look around us & realise what we have and at the end of the day, THAT is all that matters. 

Look after those we care about, be kind to those who we don’t know & just try to always make good choices 🖤

I think I’ve got this... I think I’ll be okay 🥰

#healthanxiety #anxietyawareness #mentalhealthmatters

Lockdown Recipe Series #day152

Khamang Kakdi

Today i am sharing a very delicious and famous Maharashtrian salad - Khamang Kakadi recipe with you. This (salad) koshimbir is made with Cucumber (Kakadi in Marathi) and one can sense a strong tempering in it which means Khamang and hence the name of the dish. This koshimbir recipe calls for use of fresh scrapped Coconut , roasted crushed Peanuts , finely chopped green chilies and fresh Coriander leaves apart from the main ingredient Cucumber. This mixture is then tempered with curry leaves , mustard seeds and cumin seeds and finally seasoned with lemon juice , sugar and salt.

A very refreshing and cooling summer salad , Khamang Kakadi can be made very easily and in a jiffy. It can be had as a salad , or as a side dish to the main course or just by itself as a refreshing and light mid time snacks. If we do not add the mustard seeds, hing and curry leaves, this salad can serve as a fasting food ( food for vrat) . This salad is usually paired with Sabudana khichadi.

Recipe Link: https://poonambachhav.blogspot.com/2016/05/khamang-kakadi-recipe-cucumber-salad.html
